The paper deals with problems related to curves and surfaces, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of distance measures such as Hausdorff distance, weak Frechet distance, and Frechet distance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.GR). The mention of polynomial-time solutions for some variants of the problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of NP-hardness implies that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
